headline: Uber Strikes Partnership With Baidu For Robotaxi Rollout
summary: Uber Technologies will partner with Chinese internet search leader Baidu to offer robotaxis in several markets outside of the U.S. and China this year, the companies announced Tuesday.  Uber stock fell following the news while U.S.-listed Baidu stock rallied.  Baidu will deploy thousands of its Apollo Go autonomous vehicles on Uber's platform, according to the announcement.

headline: Uber partners with China's Baidu to deploy self-driving taxis in global markets
summary: The tie-up brings together Uber's massive ride-hailing network with Baidu's fleet of more than 1,000 fully driverless vehicles across the world.  It is the latest in a series of efforts by Uber to compete in the burgeoning market as tech companies race to overcome regulatory and engineering hurdles to deploy self-driving taxis at a commercial scale.

headline: Baidu and Uber Join Forces to Accelerate Autonomous Vehicle Deployment
summary: Baidu, Inc. (NASDAQ: BIDU and HKEX: 9888) and Uber Technologies, Inc. (NYSE: UBER) today announced a multi-year strategic partnership to deploy thousands of Baidu's Apollo Go autonomous vehicles (AVs) on the Uber platform across multiple global markets outside of the U.S. and mainland China. This collaboration will focus on increasing the supply of affordable and reliable ridesharing options by bringing Baidu's advanced autonomous vehicles onto Uber's extensive network.

headline: 1 Thing That Matters Most for Tesla Stock Investors
summary: Tesla shares have boosted investors’ portfolios in the past decade, as they seem to always trade at a steep valuation.  In recent years, Tesla has been a struggling car maker, which shows glimpses of the company’s true nature.  While it has taken investors on a bumpy drive, no one can deny that Tesla (NASDAQ: TSLA) has worked out to be a wildly successful stock.
